Here's a Java solution to determine if a given integer is a power of three:

```java
class Solution {
    public boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
        // Check if n is positive and not zero
        if (n <= 0) {
            return false;
        }

        // Calculate the maximum power of 3 that fits in an integer
        int maxPowerOfThree = (int) Math.pow(3, (int) (Math.log(Integer.MAX_VALUE) / Math.log(3)));

        // Check if n is a divisor of the maximum power of 3
        return maxPowerOfThree % n == 0;
    }
}
